<body id="fire_alarm_control_panel___installation">

    <h1 class="title topictitle1" id="ariaid-title1">Fire Alarm Control Panel - Installation</h1>

    
    <div class="body taskbody"><p class="shortdesc">Installation of the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Alarm Control
                        Panel</span></em>.</p>

        <ol class="ol steps"><li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Install the new <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Alarm Control
                        Panel</span></em> and secure it with the screws (see item 2
                    in <a class="xref" href="cm_fire_alarm_control_panel___removal.html#fire_alarm_control_panel___removal__FSSCP_open">Figure 2</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Connect all wires as noted down and tighten the associated terminal block
                    screws (see item 1 in <a class="xref" href="cm_fire_alarm_control_panel___removal.html#fire_alarm_control_panel___removal__FSSCP_open">Figure 2</a>).</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Connect the battery circuit (see item 4 in <a class="xref" href="cm_fire_alarm_control_panel___removal.html#fire_alarm_control_panel___removal__FSSCP_open">Figure 2</a>) and close the cabinet door.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Test the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Controls System</span></em>, to ensure, the
                    new <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Alarm Control
                        Panel</span></em> works
                    properly.</span>
            </li>
<li class="li step">
                <span class="ph cmd">Switch the <em class="ph i"><span class="ph">Fire Alarm System</span></em> in the active mode.</span>
            </li>
</ol>

    </div>

